\begin{align*}
x^2 + 8x - 1 &= 0 \\
x^2 + 8x &= 1 \\
\end{align*}
Next, we need to add a term to both sides of the equation to complete the square on the left side. To do this, we take half of the coefficient of $x$, which is 8, divide it by 2 to get 4, and then square it to get 16.
\begin{align*}
x^2 + 8x + 16 &= 1 + 16 \\
(x + 4)^2 &= 17 \\
\end{align*}
Thus, $b = \boxed{17}$.
